<body>
<div class="container">
        <div class="content">
<div>
	<div>
		<p><b>LEASE AGREEMENT<br/></b> <br/></p>
		<p> <br/>This Vehicle Lease Agreement is made and effective from {{$bookingStartDate}} UTC (&#8220;Effective Date&#8221; or the<br/>&#8220;<b>Booking Start Date</b>&#8221;) as reflected in the booking details on the App (the &#8220; <b>Agreement</b>&#8221;)<br/></p>
		<p> <br/><b>BETWEEN<br/></b> <br/>Mr./Ms. <b>{{$ownerName}}</b> (hereinafter referred to as the <b>&#8220;Host&#8221; or &#8220;Lessor&#8221;</b>) <b>ONE PART </b> and further details of the<br/>Lessor are captured in the App .<br/><b> <br/>AND<br/></b> <br/>Mr./Ms. <b>{{$name}}</b> (hereinafter referred to as the <b>&#8220;Guest&#8221; or &#8220;Lessee&#8221;</b>) which <b>OTHER PART</b>and<br/>captured in the App.<br/> <br/> <br/>The Host and the Guest shall be hereinafter collectively referred to as &#8220; <b>Parties </b>&#8221; and individually as the &#8220; <b>Party </b>&#8221;.<br/><b>WHEREAS:<br/></b>a.        The Host is the sole legal, beneficial, and registered owner of the vehicle bearing registration number<br/></p>
		<p>{{$vehicleRegistrationNo}} {{-- with Chassis No. {{$vehicleChassisNo}} --}} (hereinafter referred to as the &#8220;<b>Vehicle</b>&#8221;).<br/> <br/></p>
		<p>b . The Host had listed the Vehicle for leasing on the Platform (defined below) subject to the terms and<br/>conditions specified therein.<br/></p>
		<p> <br/>c. Guest, a user of the Platform, wishes to lease the Vehicle from the Host and has placed upon a request<br/></p>
		<p>through the Platform/App the booking details bearing details booking id:- <b>{{$bookingId}}</b><br/> <br/></p>
		<p>d. The Lessor is willing to lease it to the Guest, subject to the terms and conditions of this Agreement and the<br/>policies mentioned upon the Platform.<br/></p>
		<p> <br/><b> <br/></b></p>
		<p><b>NOW THEREFORE IT IS AGREED </b>as follows:<br/><b>1. </b>          <b>Definition and Interpretation<br/></b> <br/>1.1.       In this Agreement, unless the context otherwise requires, the following expressions have the following<br/></p>
		<p>meanings:<br/>(i)              &#8220; <b>Applicable Laws&#8221; </b>means all applicable Indian statutes, enactments, acts of the state legislature<br/></p>
		<p>or parliament, laws, ordinances, rules, bye-laws, regulations, notifications, guidelines, policies,<br/>directions, directives and orders of any governmental authority, statutory authority, tribunal, board,<br/>court, as may be applicable . Without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing, Applicable Laws<br/>shall include laws, regulations, rules and/or ordinances of lawfully constituted authorities relating to<br/>the possession, use, storage and transport of the Vehicle, including the MVA.<br/> <br/></p>
		<p>(ii) <b>&#8220;App&#8221; </b>shall mean the Velriders mobile application for car sharing, owned and operated by Shailesh Car & Bike Private Limited which displays the booking details, Lessor /Lessee details and other details with<br/>respect to any vehicle being leased from the Platform.<br/> <br/></p>
		<p>(iii)&#8220;<b> Motor Vehicles Act </b>&#8221; or &#8220;<b>MVA</b>&#8221; means Motor Vehicles Act, 1988 , rules and regulations<br/>prescribed thereunder, as now enacted or as the same may from time to time be amended, replaced<br/>or re-enacted;<br/> <br/></p>
		<p>(iv)  &#8220;<b>Platform</b>&#8221; collectively refers to the website and mobile application by the name and style of</p>
	</div>
</div>
<div>
	<div>
		<p>Velriders Host Services available on the website of www.velriders.com , owned and operated by<br/>Shailesh Car & Bike Private Limited which includes its marketplace feature/sectionthat<br/> <br/></p>
		<p>(v)             &#8220;<b> Permitted Territory </b>&#8221; shall mean entire territory of India, excluding t Ladakh and/or any travel to<br/>connected countries including but not limited to Nepal, Bhutan , Bangladesh or Pakistan etc.<br/></p>
		<p>1.2.           In this Agreement, unless the context otherwise requires:<br/>(i)       Headings used are for convenience and ease of reference only, are not part of this Agreement and<br/></p>
		<p>shall not be relevant to or affect the meaning or interpretation of this Agreement.<br/>(ii)     Words denoted in any gender shall include all genders and terms denoting people or persons shall<br/></p>
		<p>include both natural and legal persons (such as company) and vice- versa;<br/>(iii)   The terms of this Agreement shall be deemed to be binding on both Parties based on their<br/></p>
		<p>respective conduct notwithstanding any error or defect in the execution of this Agreement; and<br/>(iv)    A reference to a clause or schedule is a reference to a clause of or schedule to this Agreement and<br/></p>
		<p>a reference to this Agreement includes any of its schedules. All schedules to this Agreement and the<br/>terms thereof shall be an integral part of this Agreement.<br/></p>
		<p><b>2. </b>          <b>Agreement to Lease<br/></b> <br/></p>
		<p>2.1        Based on the covenants, assurances and representations of the Guest recorded herein, the Host hereby<br/>grants on lease and Guest hereby takes on lease the Vehicle, subject to the terms and conditions of this<br/>Agreement.<br/></p>
		<p> <br/>2.2        The Guest expressly understands and agrees that this Agreement is a lease only and all along the absolute<br/></p>
		<p>and unencumbered ownership of the Vehicle for all intent and purposes, including for regulatory<br/>requirement under the MVA, shall remain with the Host. Nothing stated herein shall be construed to be a<br/>transfer to the Guest of any ownership right, title or interest in the Vehicle, or even a right to the Guest to<br/>demand such transfer. It is hereby clarified that during the Lease Term, the Guest shall have the beneficial<br/>possession of the Vehicle as a Guest pursuant to this Agreement.<br/></p>
		<p> <br/>2.3        During the Lease Term, the Guest shall hold the Vehicle as  as a trustee of the Host and shall, at its<br/></p>
		<p>expense, protect and defend the title of Host in the Vehicle against creditors of or any person(s) claiming<br/>through Guest.<br/></p>
		<p> <br/><b>3. </b>          <b>Terms of Vehicle Usage<br/></b></p>
		<p> <br/>3.1        The Guest hereby agrees and covenants that the Vehicle shall be used in a prudent and careful manner<br/></p>
		<p>solely for the Guest&#8217;s personal use within the Permitted Territory and to that extent shall be driven only by<br/>the Guest, in strict compliance with the requirements of the Applicable Laws (the &#8220;<b>Permitted Use</b>&#8221;).<br/> <br/></p>
		<p>3.2        The Guest further agrees and acknowledges that other than the Permitted Use, all other uses of the<br/>Vehicle including the usages listed below (by the Guest and/or any other person(s) directly or indirectly<br/>acting through, authorised by or on behalf of the Guest), are strictly prohibited (the &#8220;<b>Prohibited Use</b>s&#8221;) and<br/>constitute a material breach of this Agreement :<br/></p>
		<p> <br/>(i)              Commercial use for any purpose whatsoever including usage for transportation services (goods<br/></p>
		<p>and/or passengers) involving hire and/or reward.<br/>(ii)            For providing driving lessons.<br/>(iii)           Use by any other person other than the Guest or his/her co-driver as may have been registered on<br/></p>
		<p>the Platform failing which it would amount to deliberate act on part of Guest to allow unauthorised<br/>personnel to access the Vehicle.<br/></p>
		<p>(iv)           For sports, adventure and/or participation in races, rallies, other competitive events, endurance test<br/>and similar events.</p>
	</div>
</div>
<div>
	<div>
		<p>(v)             For towing, pushing, or propelling any trailer or any other vehicle.<br/>(vi)           For commission of any crime, illegal and/or unlawful activity(ies).<br/>(vii)          For storage of any combustible, noxious or hazardous goods or any other good(s) which owing to its<br/></p>
		<p>weight and/or structure adversely affect and/or damage the Vehicles, its interior, engine and/or any of<br/>its parts thereto and/or any other vehicle(s), person(s)/object(s) in such vehicle and/or pedestrian(s)<br/>passing the Vehicle.<br/></p>
		<p>(viii)        Taking the Vehicle outside the Permitted Territory.<br/>(ix)           Any use(s) or activity(ies) that puts the Vehicle at a greater risk of damage.<br/>(x)             Any damage caused to the Vehicle due to deliberate acts of Guest or his/her co-driver.<br/>(xi)           Any use that contravenes the terms and conditions of this Agreement, terms of the insurance<br/></p>
		<p>relating to the Vehicle and/or the requirements of all Applicable Laws.<br/> <br/></p>
		<p> <br/><b>4. </b>          <b>Lease Term<br/></b>4.1        The lease of the Vehicle to the Guest shall be for a term commencing from the Effective Date or the<br/></p>
		<p>Booking Start Date and shall end as per Booking End Date as indicated in the App. Such term shall also<br/>include any extension to the Booking End Date, or any early cancellations made by the Lessee as expressly<br/>provided in the App (the &#8220;<b>Lease Term</b>&#8221;).<br/></p>
		<p> <br/>4.2        The Lease Term may be extended for such period and on such terms and conditions as may be mutually<br/></p>
		<p>agreed upon by the Parties.<br/><b>Delivery of the Vehicle<br/></b> <br/> <br/>5.1        On execution of this Agreement and subject to payment of Lease Rental by the Guest on the Platform, the<br/></p>
		<p>Host shall notify the Guest that the Vehicle is ready for delivery. The Guest shall take delivery of the Vehicle<br/>from the location notified in writing by the Host (the &#8220;Designated Location&#8221;) together with the Vehicle<br/>Key(s), original documentation of the Vehicle, including the registration certificate, Vehicle Insurance policy,<br/>Pollution Under Control (&#8220;PUC&#8221;) Certificate and other mandatory documents, if any, prescribed by the<br/>relevant authorities under Applicable Laws (the &#8220;<b>Vehicle Documentation</b>&#8221;) on the date and time of the<br/>booking. In the event where the Host has agreed to the Vehicle be subjected to home delivery to location<br/>specified by the Guest, the Guest may requests for delivery of the Vehicle to such address/location, and the<br/>Host may choose to deliver or arrange for the Vehicle to be delivered with assistance from the Platform as<br/>per the delivery charge specified in the Fee Policy mentioned on the Platform along with the Vehicle<br/>Documentation..<br/> <br/></p>
		<p>5.2        F or the security, safety, tracking and health monitoring of the Vehicle, certain devices may be installed by<br/>the Host in the Vehicle prior to its delivery to the Guest (&#8220;<b> In-Vehicle Devices </b>&#8221;).  The Guest agrees and<br/>acknowledges that the In-Vehicle Devices may require minor modification from time to time and the Guest<br/>shall provide full access of the Vehicle to the Host, or any other person appointed by the Host for the<br/>purpose of modification of such devices with reasonable prior written notice.<br/></p>
		<p> <br/>5.3        If the Guest desires to get the Vehicle delivered at the location notified by him/her, any risk, damages to<br/></p>
		<p>the Vehicle in transit to such location shall be treated as an accident case and the repair will be covered as<br/>per the provision of Clause 10 below (Insurance).<br/> <br/></p>
		<p>5.4        The Guest shall remain present in-person to [take]/ [receive] the delivery of the Vehicle, produce his/her<br/>original driving license for inspection, furnish copies of such driving license, his/her recent passport size<br/>photograph and an additional address proof document (voter ID, Aadhar card, or valid passport) and sign<br/>the necessary documents (viz., delivery receipt) at the time of delivery, which will serve as an evidence of<br/>delivery and acceptance of the Vehicle. Further, the Guest shall inspect the Vehicle (exterior walk-around<br/>and an interior look-over of the Vehicle) prior to taking delivery and shall be deemed to have satisfied<br/>himself/herself as to its condition, fitness for Guest's personal use and compliance with specified safety<br/>standards. Any fault/defect detected in the Vehicle thereafter shall be dealt with in accordance with the<br/>provisions of Clause 11 below (Addition, Maintenance and Repair) .<br/> <br/></p>
		<p>5.5        If the Guest fails to take the delivery of the Vehicle on the Booking Start Date for any reason whatsoever,<br/>the subsequent attempts to deliver the Vehicle to the Guest will be charged as per the Fee Policy . The<br/>Guest hereby agree and acknowledge that in case regardless of such failure to take the delivery of the</p>
		</div>
</div>
<div>
	<div><p>Vehicle by the Guest and consequent delay in takeover of the Vehicle by the Guest, the Lease Term shall<br/>commence from the Booking Start Date. Provided that in case of failure of the Guest to take delivery or Host<br/>to provide delivery the non-defaulting Party shall have the right to terminate this Agreement in accordance<br/>with Clause 14 below.<br/></p>
<p> <br/><b>6. </b>          <b>Lease Rental<br/></b></p>
<p><b> <br/></b>6.1        As security for the prompt and full payment for leasing of the vehicle and all other sums payable by the<br/></p>
<p>Guest hereunder, and the faithful and timely performance of all provisions of this Agreement, and any<br/>extensions or renewals thereof, the Guest shall deposit the Lease Rental in advance a sum more particularly<br/>described in the Fee Policy/booking details on the App (&#8220;<b>Lease Rental</b>&#8221;) with the Host through the Platform<br/>simultaneously with the execution of this Agreement. The same shall be payable through the Platform and<br/>shall be retained by Platform until the vehicle is returned to the Designated Location on Booking End Date.<br/><b> <br/></b></p>
<p>6.2        If the Guest terminates this Agreement before taking delivery of the Vehicle or refuses and/or is<br/>unable/unwilling for any reason to accept delivery of the Vehicle in accordance with Clause 5 above, the<br/>Host shall be entitled to terminate this Agreement in accordance with Clause 14.1 below and any advance<br/>Lease Rental shall stand forfeited to compensate the Host for the costs, charges, expenses, losses incurred<br/>by the Host arising out of such an action of the Guest. Likewise, if the Host refuses and/or is unable/unwilling<br/>for any reason to give delivery of the vehicle in accordance with Clause 5 above, the Guest shall be entitled<br/>to terminate this Agreement in accordance with Clause 14.2 below and the Lease Rental as paid in advance<br/>shall be promptly refunded to the Guest.<br/></p>
<p> <br/> <br/></p>
<p>6.3        On the expiration or earlier termination of this Agreement and return of the Vehicle to the Host (except<br/>where the Vehicle is stolen or its completely destroyed due to accident or damages), or any extension or<br/>renewal thereof, provided Guest has paid all the Lease Rental and all other amounts payable by him/her<br/>hereunder and fully performed all other provisions of this Agreement.<br/><b> <br/></b></p>
<p><b>7. </b>          <b>Lease Rental<br/> <br/></b></p>
<p>7.1        In lieu of the lease of the Vehicle and related services hereunder, the Guest shall pay to the Host a lease<br/>rental fee specified in the booking details on the App (the &#8220;Lease Rental&#8221;) at the time of booking the<br/>vehicle in advance for the Lease Term through the Platform.<br/></p>
<p> <br/>7.2        The Guest hereby agrees and acknowledges that the Lease Rental comprises of the charges towards (i)<br/></p>
<p>usage of the Vehicle for a pre-agreed mileage as specified in Booking details on the App (&#8220;Agreed<br/><b>Mileage</b>&#8221;); (ii) Platform usage fees; (iii) maintenance and repair cost; (iv) damage protection charges; and<br/>(v) delivery charges, if applicable. In the event the usage of Vehicle exceeds the Agreed Mileage, the excess<br/>mileage will be charged as per the rate specified in the Fee Policy. The difference between the actual usage<br/>i.e., lesser, or greater than the Agreed Mileage shall be determined and settled i.e., paid by the Guest to the<br/>Host or vice versa at the time of expiry or termination of the Lease Term.<br/> <br/></p>
<p>7.3        Guest shall be liable to pay any outstanding Lease Rental or other charges accruing due to Guest<br/>exceeding Agreed Mileage or otherwise and shall be chargeable in accordance with the Fee Policy and may<br/>also incur penalties or late payment charges for prolonged default in clearing such outstanding amount as<br/>mentioned in the Fee Policy.<br/></p>
<p> <br/>7.4        Any other payments made by the Host on behalf of the Guest pertaining to the Vehicle, under this<br/></p>
<p>Agreement or otherwise shall be promptly reimbursed by the Guest to Host on receipt of written notice in<br/>respect thereof from the Host together with documentary proof of such payments or at the option of the<br/>Host, to set off against amounts, if any, from the Host to the Guest.<br/> <br/></p>
<p><b>8. </b>          <b>Theft and Accident<br/> <br/></b></p>
<p>8.1        Guest will be solely responsible for safety measures/ precautions against any damage, accident, or<br/>criminal activity on/of the Vehicle and subject to provisions of Clause 10 (Insurance) the Guest assumes sole<br/>financial liability during the term of this Agreement in respect of:</p>
</div>
</div>
<div><div><p> <br/>(i)              in case the Vehicle is damaged, destroyed or stolen, however caused, or occasioned ;<br/>(ii)            in case the Vehicle is damaged, destroyed or stolen due to the deliberate act of Guest or his/her co-<br/></p>
<p>driver; and<br/>(iii)           for all other risks and liabilities, including personal injury or death and property damage, arising with<br/></p>
<p>respect to the Vehicle, howsoever arising.<br/> <br/>The Guest hereby agrees and acknowledges that under no circumstances shall the Host be held liable to the<br/>Guest and/or any third party(ies) for any (i) any loss or damage that may be suffered by the Guest or any<br/>third party(ies) arising from the above events or risks, howsoever caused, or occasioned; and (ii) indirect,<br/>incidental, special, or consequential damages arising from or related the use of Vehicle by the Guest or<br/>his/her co-passenger or family members. <br/></p>
<p> <br/>8.2        In the event of damage, accident or theft of the Vehicle or any part and/or accessory thereof, the Guest:<br/></p>
<p> <br/>(i)              shall immediately, but in no event later than [24] hours from the occurrence of damage, accident, or<br/></p>
<p>theft, notify the Platform and the Host all details of the damage, accident or theft in writing;<br/> <br/></p>
<p>(ii)            extend full support and cooperation to the Host in reporting the damage, accident or theft to the<br/>nearest police station and obtain a copy of the first information report (&#8220;<b>FIR</b>&#8221;);<br/></p>
<p> <br/>(iii)          in case of damage or accident, after filing the FIR and notifying the damage or accident to the Host,<br/></p>
<p>as per Host&#8217;s instruction take the Vehicle to the nearest workshop specified by the Host for repair or<br/>assessment of repairability.<br/></p>
<p>In case of failure to fulfill its obligation under this Clause 8.2, the Guest shall be solely liable for all costs,<br/>damages and/or consequences arising as a result thereof.<br/></p>
<p>8.3        In the case of:<br/> <br/></p>
<p>(i)              theft, accident or damage resulting in complete destruction/loss of the Vehicle, the Guest shall be liable to<br/>pay the monthly Lease Rental till such time as the claim in respect of such theft, accident or damage until<br/>such claims is duly is settled by the insurance company (if any). In absence of the insurance company, the<br/>Guest is solely and fully liable to make good the damages suffered by the Host.<br/>(ii)            accident or damage resulting in partial or repairable damages in the Vehicle, the Guest shall be<br/></p>
<p>liable to continue to pay the Lease Rental in accordance with this Agreement, including for the period<br/>during which the Vehicle is deposited with any workshop for repair work.<br/></p>
<p>(iii) accident or damage caused to the Vehicle due to deliberate acts of Guest or his/her co-driver, Guest<br/>acknowledges and agrees to compensate Host for all the damages caused to the Vehicle due to such deliberate<br/>acts during the Lease Term. Such relief shall be in addition to Host&#8217;s rights and remedies otherwise available at<br/>law.<br/></p>
<p> <br/>8.4        Notwithstanding anything contained herein, in the case of an accident or damage resulting in partial or<br/></p>
<p>repairable damages to the Vehicle or in case of theft where the Vehicle is recovered before or after the claim<br/>amount under insurance is received from the insurance company:<br/></p>
<p> <br/>(i)              the Host may in its sole discretion depending on the condition of the Vehicle, opt not to continue the<br/></p>
<p>lease of Vehicle and terminate this Agreement under Clause 14.1 below and the Guest shall be liable<br/>to promptly pay all unpaid dues under the Agreement to the Host including without limitation the<br/>charges for such repairs carried out or the cost of the vehicle ( in case of a complete damage or theft),</p>

</div></div>
<div><div><p>Excess Mileage Charges;<br/> <br/></p>
<p>(ii)            the Guest shall not be entitled to terminate the Agreement and where the Lease Term is about to<br/>expiry the same will stand extended, until the settlement of the damage claim and/or conclusion of<br/>the police investigation and/or proceeding(s) by any other competent authority(ies) with respect to<br/>the damage, accident or theft of the Vehicle.<br/></p>
<p><b> <br/>9. </b>          <b>Traffic Violation and Confiscation<br/></b></p>
<p><b> <br/></b>9.1        During the Lease Term and until the return of the Vehicle in good working order/condition to the Host, the<br/></p>
<p>Guest is solely responsible for use of the Vehicle in compliance with traffic rules and regulation, including<br/>payment of toll charges. Accordingly, the Guest shall be solely liable for all traffic violations involving the<br/>Vehicle during the aforesaid period (the &#8220;Traffic Violation &#8221;) and cost, penalty, fines and/or charges<br/>imposed in respect thereof, including fines for late payment, toll evasion/ interstate taxes or any processing<br/>fees added by the relevant regulatory authority(ies). The Traffic Violation includes, but is not limited to,<br/>unauthorised parking, excess speeding, breaking red light, photo enforcement, and toll violations.<br/> <br/></p>
<p>9.2        The Guest shall notify/report all Traffic Violations to the Host in writing together with all details, as soon as<br/>possible, not being later than 24 hours prior to expiry of period prescribed for taking necessary action in<br/>respect thereof under Applicable Laws (for example, if the case is being taken to court). Thereafter, the<br/>Guest shall forthwith pay the relevant fine/s to the authority concerned and provide Host with the proof of<br/>such payment. In the event the Guest fails to do so, the Host shall have the right at its sole discretion to pay<br/>such amounts and the Guest shall reimburse the Host for same at the earliest.<br/></p>
<p> <br/>9.3        The Guest shall also be responsible if the Vehicle is confiscated, seized or impounded during the Lease<br/></p>
<p>Term and until the return of the Vehicle in good working condition to the Host, for any reason attributable to<br/>the Guest (&#8220;Confiscation&#8221;). In such cases the Guest shall notify/report the Confiscation to the Host in<br/>writing together with all details, as soon as possible, not being later than 24 hours prior to the expiry of the<br/>period prescribed for taking necessary action in respect thereof under Applicable Laws. The Guest shall<br/>provide full support, assistance and cooperation to the Host then take all necessary steps/actions, to have<br/>the Vehicle released from the relevant authorities. In case Host assists in the release of the Vehicle from<br/>Confiscation, including payment of fines, charges, penalty, and fees imposed by relevant authority and all<br/>the costs and expenses incidental thereto. In the event the Guest fails to provide its support and/or pay for<br/>the cost involved in having the Vehicle released from Confiscation, the Host shall have the right (at its sole<br/>discretion) to take necessary steps to secure the release of the Vehicle at its own expense. In such cases<br/>the Guest shall promptly reimburse the Host for all cost/expense incurred for release of the Vehicle.<br/> <br/></p>
<p>9.4        Notwithstanding anything to the contrary stated herein, in case of Confiscation (i) if the Lease Term is<br/>about to expire prior to release of the Vehicle, the Lease Term will stand extended in accordance with the<br/>terms of this Agreement; and (ii) the Guest shall not be entitled to terminate the Agreement, until the<br/>Vehicle has been duly released, fines/charges/conditions, if any, imposed for release of Vehicle by the<br/>relevant authorities has been paid or satisfied/fulfilled and necessary documentary evidence reflecting<br/>conclusive disposal of the matter is received by the Host.<br/> <br/></p>
<p><b>10. </b>       <b>Insurance<br/> <br/></b></p>
<p>10.1     Host shall at its own expense during the Lease Term and until the Vehicle is delivered back in good<br/>working condition, comprehensively insure the Vehicle with an insurance company of its choice (&#8220;<b> Vehicle<br/>Insurance </b>&#8221;).<br/> <br/></p>
<p>10.2     The Vehicle Insurance will   provide primary third-party liability protection, which will be to the extent of<br/>claims / liabilities covered by the Vehicle insurer on the Vehicles for any/ all claims and/or liabilities arising</p>

</div></div>
<div><div><p>during the use or operation of the Vehicle by the Guest.<br/> <br/></p>
<p> <br/>10.3     This shall not however cover the Own Damage and the Guest will be responsible for any associated costs<br/></p>
<p>and charges directly/indirectly personally attributable to the Guest&#8217;s default with the terms of this<br/>Agreement. However, it is hereby clarified that if this third-party liability protection is extended by the Host,<br/>it will not be applicable if the liability arises due to Guest&#8217; negligence, or breach of applicable terms under<br/>this Agreement.<br/></p>
<p> <br/>10.4     The liability protection under the Vehicle Insurance applies only to claims of third-party bodily injury,<br/></p>
